<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolev seadus reguleerib t&ouml;&ouml;otsijale ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>This Act regulates the provision of employment services to persons who seek employment and to employers. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduses kasutatakse m&otilde;isteid j&auml;rgmises t&auml;henduses: </eesti>
<inglise>In this Act, the following definitions are used: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenus on teenus t&ouml;&ouml;otsijale t&ouml;&ouml; leidmise ja t&ouml;&ouml;alase arengu soodustamiseks ning t&ouml;&ouml;andjale sobiva t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;u saamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) employment service means a service to persons who seek employment to assist them in finding employment and to promote professional development, and to employers to assist them in finding suitable labour force; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;otsija on isik, kelle on registreerinud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja ja kes otsib t&ouml;&ouml;d; </eesti>
<inglise>2) person who seeks employment is a person who is registered with an employment service provider and who seeks employment; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tu on t&ouml;&ouml;otsija t&ouml;&ouml;tu sotsiaalse kaitse seaduse &sect; 3 l&otilde;ike 1 t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise>3) unemployed person is a person who seeks employment within the meaning of subsection 3 (1) of the Social Protection of the Unemployed Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) pikaajaline t&ouml;&ouml;tu on isik, kes on olnud t&ouml;&ouml;tuna arvel &uuml;le 12 kuu; </eesti>
<inglise>4) long-term unemployed is a person who has been registered as unemployed for longer than twelve months; </inglise>
<eesti>5) sobiv t&ouml;&ouml; on t&ouml;&ouml;, mida t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveamet peab isikule kohaseks tema haridust, erialaoskusi, t&ouml;&ouml;kogemust, terviseseisundit, soolist sobivust ning elukoha ja t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskoha vahemaad arvestades. </eesti>
<inglise>5) suitable work means employment which an employment office deems suitable for a person considering his or her education, occupational qualifications, work experience, state of health, sex and the distance of the place of residence from the place of work. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Types of employment service </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse liigid on: </eesti>
<inglise>The types of employment service are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teavitamine t&ouml;&ouml;turu olukorrast ja t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolituse v&otilde;imalustest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) informing of the situation in the labour market and of the possibilities of employment training; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;vahendus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) employment mediation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolitus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) vocational training; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kutsen&otilde;ustamine; </eesti>
<inglise>4) vocational guidance; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetus ettev&otilde;tluse alustamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>5) employment subsidy to start a business; </inglise>
<eesti>6) t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetus t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&auml;iksema konkurentsiv&otilde;imega t&ouml;&ouml;tu t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>6) employment subsidy to employers to employ less competitive unemployed persons; </inglise>
<eesti>7) h&auml;daabit&ouml;&ouml;. </eesti>
<inglise>7) community placements. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja </eesti>
<inglise>Employment service providers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 3 loetletud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuseid osutavad t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employment offices shall provide employment services listed in &sect; 3 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Era&otilde;iguslikul juriidilisel isikul ja &auml;riregistrisse kantud f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjal on &otilde;igus osutada &sect; 3 punktides 1-4 loetletud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuseid. </eesti>
<inglise>Legal persons in private law and sole proprietors entered in the commercial register have the right to provide employment services listed in clauses 3 1) -4). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigi t&ouml;&ouml;turuasutused on Sotsiaalministeeriumi valitsemisalas tegutsevad T&ouml;&ouml;turuamet ja selle kohalikud asutused - t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) State employment agencies are the Labour Market Board and its regional offices within the area of government of the Ministry of Social Affairs - employment offices. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Era&otilde;iguslikul juriidilisel isikul ja &auml;riregistrisse kantud f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjal peab t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste osutamiseks olema tegevusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Legal persons in private law and sole proprietors entered in the commercial register must hold activity licences for the provision of employment services. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenusele </eesti>
<inglise>Right to use employment services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenusele t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametis on t&ouml;&ouml;andjal ja t&ouml;&ouml;otsijal, kes on Eesti alaline elanik v&otilde;i Eestis viibiv pagulane. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers and persons who seek employment who are permanent residents of Estonia or refugees staying in Estonia have the right to use employment services provided by employment offices. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 3 punktides 1, 2 ja 6 nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employers have the right to use employment services specified in clauses 3 1), 2) and 6) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;tul on &otilde;igus k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 3 punktides 1-5 ja 7 nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Unemployed persons have the right to use employment services specified in clauses 3 1) -5) and 7) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise kohta teate saanud t&ouml;&ouml;tajal on &otilde;igus k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 3 punktides 1-4 nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employee who receives a notice concerning termination of the employment contract has the right to use employment services specified in clauses 3 1) -4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) V&otilde;rdselt Eesti alalise elanikuga on &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenustele t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametis Eestis elaval v&auml;lismaalasel, kellel on t&auml;htajaline elamisluba kehtivusega kuni viis aastat, kuid mitte kauem kui 2001. aasta 12. juulini. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Aliens residing in Estonia who have temporary residence permits for a term of five years, but for not longer than until 12 July 2001 have the right to use employment services provided by employment offices on equal basis with permanent residents of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Teistel Eestis t&auml;htajalise elamisloa alusel viibivatel v&auml;lismaalastel on &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametis k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 3 punktides 1 ja 2 nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenustele, kui v&auml;lislepinguga ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Other aliens staying in Estonia on the basis of temporary residence permits have the right to use employment services specified in clauses 3 1) and 2) of this Act in employment offices unless otherwise provided by an international agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste osutamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Principles of provision of employment services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenus peab soodustama t&ouml;&ouml;otsija t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendumist ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjal sobiva t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;u saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employment services shall facilitate the engagement in employment of persons who seek employment and assist employers in finding suitable labour force. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenust osutades l&auml;htutakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja vajadustest ja &otilde;igusest vabalt valida endale t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;udu ning t&ouml;&ouml;otsija vajadustest ja &otilde;igusest vabalt valida t&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The provision of employment services shall be based on the needs and rights of employers to freely choose their labour force and on the needs and right of persons who seek employment to freely choose work. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenust osutades v&otilde;etakse arvesse t&ouml;&ouml;turu olukorda ja prognoose selle kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon provision of employment services, situation in the labour market and forecasts concerning it shall be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenust osutades teevad koost&ouml;&ouml;d riigi t&ouml;&ouml;turuasutused ning era&otilde;iguslikust juriidilisest isikust v&otilde;i &auml;riregistrisse kantud f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjatest t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste osutajad, arvestades t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate organisatsioonide ettepanekutega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon provision of employment services, state employment offices and employment service providers who are legal persons in private law or sole proprietors entered in the commercial register shall act in co-operation, taking into account the proposals of organisations of employers and employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenust osutades ei tohi teha eelistusi ega piirata t&ouml;&ouml;otsija &otilde;igusi, l&auml;htudes tema rahvusest, soost, vanusest, puude liigist, seksuaalsest orientatsioonist, nahav&auml;rvist, rassist, sotsiaalsest p&auml;ritolust, &uuml;hiskondlikust seisundist, usulistest, poliitilistest v&otilde;i muudest veendumustest ega t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;tjate v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjate huvide esindamisest, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui see on ette n&auml;htud teiste seadustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon provision of employment services, preferences shall not be given, and the rights of persons who seek employment shall not be restricted on the grounds of their nationality, sex, age, type of disability, sexual orientation, colour, race, social origin, social status, religion, political or other beliefs, or representation of the interests of employees or employers, unless it is prescribed by other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse eest tasumine </eesti>
<inglise>Payment for employment services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveamet osutab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 3 loetletud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuseid t&ouml;&ouml;otsijale ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale tasuta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employment offices shall provide employment services listed in &sect; 3 of this Act to persons who seek employment and to employers without charge. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Era&otilde;iguslik juriidiline isik ja &auml;riregistrisse kantud f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja osutavad t&ouml;&ouml;otsijale t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenust tasuta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Legal persons in private law and sole proprietors entered in the commercial register shall provide employment services to persons who seek employment without charge. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveamet, era&otilde;iguslik juriidiline isik ja &auml;riregistrisse kantud f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja osutavad meremeestele t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenust nende t&ouml;&ouml;lev&auml;rbamisel ja -paigutamisel tasuta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Employment offices, legal persons in private law and sole proprietors entered in the commercial register shall provide employment services to seafarers upon recruitment and placement thereof without charge. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste osutamise arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Keeping records on provision of employment services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;turuamet peab t&ouml;&ouml;otsijate ja t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste riiklikku registrit (edaspidi register), mis sisaldab andmeid t&ouml;&ouml;otsijate, sealhulgas t&ouml;&ouml;tute, t&ouml;&ouml;tuna arveloleku aja ja t&ouml;&ouml;tule makstud toetuste ning osutatud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste kohta, ning Eestis t&ouml;&ouml;tamiseks n&otilde;usolekut taotlenud v&auml;lismaalaste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Labour Market Board shall maintain a state register of persons who seek employment and of employment services (hereinafter register) which contains information on persons who seek employment, including unemployed persons, periods of registration as unemployed, and benefits paid and employment services provided to unemployed persons, and on aliens who have applied for permission to work in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>Era&otilde;iguslik t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja peab t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse andmekogu (edaspidi andmekogu), mis sisaldab andmeid t&ouml;&ouml;otsijate ja osutatud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Employment service providers in private law shall maintain databases of employment services (hereinafter database) which contain information on persons who seek employment and on employment services provided. </inglise>
<eesti>Andmekogu ja registri andmeid t&ouml;&ouml;deldakse ja kogutakse andmekogude seaduse (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77) ja isikuandmete kaitse seaduse (RT I 1996, 48, 944; 1998, 59, 941; 111, 1833; 2000, 50, 317; 92, 597; 104, 685; 2001, 50, 283) kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>Data in the databases and register shall be processed and collected pursuant to the Databases Act (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77) and the Personal Data Protection Act (RT I 1996, 48, 944; 1998, 59, 941; 111, 1833; 2000, 50, 317; 92, 597; 104, 685; 2001, 50, 283). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Registri eesm&auml;rk on andmete tagamine T&ouml;&ouml;turuametile k&auml;esoleva seaduse, t&ouml;&ouml;tu sotsiaalse kaitse seaduse ja teiste seadustega pandud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The purpose of the register is to ensure the availability of data for the performance of functions imposed on the Labour Market Board by this Act, the Social Protection of the Unemployed Act and other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Registri asutab Vabariigi Valitsus sotsiaalministri ettepanekul andmekogude seadusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The register shall be established by the Government of the Republic on the proposal of the Minister of Social Affairs pursuant to the procedure established by the Databases Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Andmete kandmine registrisse ja andmete saamine registrist toimub vastavalt k&auml;esolevale seadusele, andmekogude seadusele, isikuandmete kaitse seadusele, sotsiaalmaksuseadusele, t&ouml;&ouml;tu sotsiaalse kaitse seadusele ja teistele &otilde;igusaktidele ning riikliku t&ouml;&ouml;otsijate ja t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste registri pidamise p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusele, mille kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Data shall be entered in and received from the register pursuant to this Act, the Databases Act, the Personal Data Protection Act, the Social Tax Act, the Social Protection of the Unemployed Act and other legislation and the statutes for maintenance of the state register of persons who seek employment and of employment services, which are approved by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 59, 359) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 59, 359) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Registri vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja on T&ouml;&ouml;turuamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The chief processor of the register is the Labour Market Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Register sisaldab: </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The register shall contain the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isikut identifitseerivaid andmeid, mille aluseks on rahvastiku arvestuse andmebaas. </eesti>
<inglise>1) data identifying persons, based on data in the population registration database. </inglise>
<eesti>Isik loetakse registrisse kantuks, kui teda identifitseerivad andmed on registrisse kantud kas rahvastiku arvestuse andmebaasi v&otilde;i passi alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>A person is deemed to be entered in the register if data identifying him or her has been entered in the register on the basis of the population registration database or his or her passport; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isiku &uuml;ldandmeid, mille allikregistriks on rahvastiku arvestuse andmebaas; </eesti>
<inglise>2) general data concerning persons, based on data in the population registration database; </inglise>
<eesti>3) andmeid isiku hariduse, kodakondsuse, soo, t&ouml;&ouml;kogemuse, vastun&auml;idustuste kohta teatud t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks ning v&auml;lismaalase puhul andmeid tema Eestis viibimise aluse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) information on persons' education, citizenship, sex, professional experience, contraindications for performing certain work, and information on the bases for the stay in Estonia in the case of aliens; </inglise>
<eesti>4) andmeid isikule osutatud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste, m&auml;&auml;ratud ja makstud t&ouml;&ouml;tu riikliku abiraha, &otilde;ppestipendiumi ja &uuml;hekordse toetuse ning t&ouml;&ouml;tuna arveloleku aja kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>4) information concerning employment services provided, state unemployment benefits, stipends and single benefits granted and paid to persons, and the periods of registration as unemployed. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 3 punktides 2-7 nimetatud teenuse osutaja kannab andmekogusse t&ouml;&ouml;otsija isikuandmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A service provider specified in clauses 3 2) -7) of this Act shall enter the personal data of a person who seeks employment in the database. </inglise>
<eesti>Need on: nimi, s&uuml;nniaeg, isikukood, elukoht, kodakondsus, sugu, isiku t&ouml;&ouml;kogemus, vastun&auml;idustused teatud t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks ja haridus ning v&auml;lismaalase puhul tema Eestis viibimise &otilde;iguslik alus. </eesti>
<inglise>The personal data are: name, date of birth, personal identification code, place of residence, citizenship, sex, person's professional experience, contraindications for performing certain work, education, and in the case of an alien, the legal basis for his or her stay in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Era&otilde;iguslik t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja v&otilde;ib andmekogusse kantud t&ouml;&ouml;otsija isikuandmeid ja andmeid osutatud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste kohta avaldada ainult isiku n&otilde;usolekul t&ouml;&ouml;andjale ja seadustega etten&auml;htud korras teistele asutustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Employment service providers in private law may disclose the personal data of a person who seeks employment and is entered in the database and information on employment services provided to the person to employers only with the consent of the person and to other agencies pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Era&otilde;iguslik t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja kustutab andmekogust isikuandmed p&auml;rast seda, kui isik on leidnud t&ouml;&ouml;koha v&otilde;i on andmete kustutamiseks esitanud avalduse. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Employment service providers in private law shall delete personal data from the database after the person finds employment or submits an application for deletion of the data. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Statistiliste ja teaduslike uuringute jaoks andmete esitamise korra kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the procedure for submission of information for statistical and scientific studies. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametile vabadest t&ouml;&ouml;kohtadest ja t&ouml;&ouml;suhte l&otilde;petamisest teatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notice to employment office of vacant jobs and termination of employment relationship </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud teatama t&ouml;&ouml;taja elukohaj&auml;rgsele t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametile kavandatavast t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisest hiljemalt j&auml;rgmisel p&auml;eval, kui ta on sellest teatanud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer is required to notify the employment office of the residence of the employee of the planned termination of the employment contract not later than on the following day after the employer notifies the employee thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja teatab t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametile vabadest t&ouml;&ouml;kohtadest, kuhu on kavas t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tta uusi t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid, v&auml;lja arvatud t&ouml;&ouml;kohad, mis t&auml;idetakse seaduses v&otilde;i Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;ruses etten&auml;htud juhtudel avaliku konkursi v&otilde;i valimise teel v&otilde;i kuhu t&ouml;&ouml;andja on juba leidnud sobiva kandidaadi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer shall notify an employment office of vacant positions in which the employer plans to hire new employees, except positions which in the cases prescribed by an Act or a regulation of the Government of the Republic are filled by way of public competition or election, or for which the employer has already found a suitable candidate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vabast t&ouml;&ouml;kohast teatades esitab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametile andmed, mille p&otilde;hjal t&ouml;&ouml;otsija saab teavet pakutavast t&ouml;&ouml;st, t&ouml;&ouml;tajale esitatavatest kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;uetest ja t&ouml;&ouml;tingimustest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon giving notice of a vacant job, an employer shall submit to an employment office information on the basis of which a person who seeks employment can obtain information concerning the offered job, qualification requirements for the employees and working conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;andja teatab t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametile vaba t&ouml;&ouml;koha t&auml;itmisest hiljemalt j&auml;rgmisel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employer shall notify an employment office of filling a vacant position not later than on the following working day. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse tegevusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Employment Services Activity Licence </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse tegevusloa andmise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for issue of employment services activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse tegevusluba on dokument, mis annab &otilde;iguse selles m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employment services activity licence is a document which grants the right to provide the employment services indicated therein. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse tegevusloa vormi kehtestab ja tegevusloa annab v&auml;lja sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the format of the activity licences and shall issue the activity licences. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse tegevusloa taotlemiseks tuleb sotsiaalministrile esitada avaldus, milles m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to apply for an employment services activity licence, an application shall be submitted to the Minister of Social Affairs, which shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) taotleja nimi ja aadress ning telefoni ja faksi olemasolul ka nende numbrid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name and address of the applicant, and telephone and facsimile numbers if any; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenused, mille osutamiseks tegevusluba taotletakse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the employment services for the provision of which the activity licence is being applied; </inglise>
<eesti>3) avalduse t&auml;itnud isiku nimi ja allkiri ning ametikoht. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the name, signature and position of the person who completes the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud avaldusele lisatakse j&auml;rgmised andmed ja dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following information and documents shall be appended to an application specified in subsection (2) of this section: </inglise>
<eesti>1) asutamislepingu v&otilde;i asutamisotsuse &auml;rakiri; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a copy of the memorandum of association or foundation resolution; </inglise>
<eesti>2) Maksuameti t&otilde;end avansiliste maksete maksjana registreerimise kohta v&otilde;i &auml;riregistri t&otilde;end f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjana registreerimise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a statement from the Tax Board concerning registration as payer of advance payments or a certificate of the commercial register concerning registration as sole proprietor; </inglise>
<eesti>3) p&otilde;hikiri; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the statutes or articles of association; </inglise>
<eesti>4) registrikood; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the registry code; </inglise>
<eesti>5) Maksuameti &otilde;iend maksuv&otilde;lgnevuse puudumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a certificate from the Tax Board confirming the absence of tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kviitung riigil&otilde;ivu tasumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a receipt for payment of the state fee; </inglise>
<eesti>7) andmekaitse j&auml;relevalveasutuses delikaatsete isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise registreerimise andmed; </eesti>
<inglise>7) information concerning registration of processing of sensitive personal data with the data protection supervision authority; </inglise>
<eesti>8) esindaja olemasolul volikiri. </eesti>
<inglise>8) an authorisation document in the case of a representative. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Sotsiaalministril v&otilde;i tema volitatud Sotsiaalministeeriumi t&ouml;&ouml;tajal on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda tegevusloa taotlejalt kavandatava t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutamise kohta lisateavet ning kontrollida esitatud andmete &otilde;igsust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Social Affairs or an employee of the Ministry of Social Affairs authorised by the Minister has the right to request additional information from an applicant for an activity licence concerning the planned provision of employment services and to verify the authenticity of submitted information. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tegevusloa andmise v&otilde;i andmisest keeldumise otsustab sotsiaalminister avalduse saamisest alates &uuml;he kuu jooksul ja teatab sellest taotlejale kirjalikult otsuse tegemisest alates k&uuml;mne p&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Minister of Social Affairs shall decide on the issue of or refusal to issue an activity licence within one month as of receipt of an application and shall notify the applicant of the decision in writing within ten days after the decision is made. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa andmisest keeldumise otsus peab sisaldama keeldumise p&otilde;hjendust. </eesti>
<inglise>A decision to refuse to issue an activity licence shall contain the reasons for refusal. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Tegevusluba antakse kolmeks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Activity licences shall be issued for three years. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse tegevusloa andmisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Refusal to issue employment services activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba ei anta, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>An activity licence shall not be issued if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avaldus ja sellele lisatud dokumendid ei ole k&auml;esoleva seaduse n&otilde;uete kohased; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the application and appended documents are not in conformity with the requirements of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste osutamine ei ole juriidilise isiku p&otilde;hikirjaj&auml;rgne tegevusala v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja &auml;riregistrisse kantud tegevusala; </eesti>
<inglise>2) provision of employment services does not fall in the area of activity specified in the statutes or articles of association of the legal person or the area of activity of the sole proprietor entered in the commercial register; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tegevusloa taotleja on maksuv&otilde;lglane; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the applicant for the activity licence owes tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tegevusloa taotlejale on v&auml;lja kuulutatud pankrot; </eesti>
<inglise>4) bankruptcy of the applicant for the activity licence is declared; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tegevusloa taotleja eelmine tegevusluba on tunnistatud kehtetuks &otilde;igusnormide rikkumise t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the previous activity licence of the applicant for the activity licence has been revoked due to violation of rules of law; </inglise>
<eesti>6) taotleja karistusandmed dokumentide v&otilde;i andmete v&otilde;ltsimise, h&auml;vitamise v&otilde;i andmet&ouml;&ouml;tlusalaste kuritegude eest ei ole karistusregistrist kustutatud; </eesti>
<inglise>6) information concerning punishment of the applicant for falsification or destruction of documents or data, or for criminal offences relating to data processing has not been expunged from the punishment register; </inglise>
<eesti>7) delikaatsete isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine on andmekaitse j&auml;relevalveasutuses registreerimata. </eesti>
<inglise>7) the processing of sensitive personal data is not registered with a data protection supervision authority. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of employment services activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa andja tunnistab loa kehtetuks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>The issuer of an activity licence shall revoke a licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tegevusloa taotlemisel on t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja esitanud valeandmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the employment service provider submitted false information upon application for the activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja tegevuses ilmnevad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 11 punktides 2 ja 4 nimetatud asjaolud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) facts specified in clauses 11 2) and 4) of this Act become evident in the activities of the employment service provider; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja tegevus ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja teiste &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the activities of the employment service provider are not in compliance with the requirements of this Act or other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse tegevusloa pikendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Extension of employment services activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse tegevusloa pikendamiseks esitab selle taotleja sotsiaalministrile k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 10 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 loetletud andmed ja dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>In order to extend an employment services activity licence, an applicant shall submit the information and documents listed in subsections 10 (2) and (3) of this Act to the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa pikendamine vaadatakse l&auml;bi samas korras kui tegevusloa v&auml;ljastamine. </eesti>
<inglise>Extension of activity licences shall be reviewed pursuant to the same procedure as issue of activity licences. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalve t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutamise &uuml;le </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision over provision of employment services </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalvet t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste osutamise &uuml;le teostab t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse tegevusloa v&auml;ljaandja Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Agencies which issue employment services activity licences shall exercise supervision over the provision of employment services pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenused </eesti>
<inglise>Employment Services </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Teavitamine t&ouml;&ouml;turu olukorrast ja t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolituse v&otilde;imalustest </eesti>
<inglise>Giving information on situation in labour market and of possibilities of employment training </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teavitamine t&ouml;&ouml;turu olukorrast ja t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolituse v&otilde;imalustest on teabe andmine t&ouml;&ouml;turu seisust, muudatustest ja prognoosidest, koolitajatest ning &otilde;petatavatest erialadest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Giving information on the situation in the labour market and of the possibilities of employment training means providing information about the conditions of the labour market, changes and forecasts, training providers and vocations to be trained. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;turu olukorrast ja t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolituse v&otilde;imalustest teavitamise eesm&auml;rk on anda &uuml;levaade t&ouml;&ouml;turust, t&ouml;&ouml;kohtadest ja neil t&ouml;&ouml;tamiseks esitatavatest n&otilde;uetest ning t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolituse v&otilde;imalustest sobivaima t&ouml;&ouml;koha v&otilde;i otstarbekaima t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse valimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The purpose of giving information on the situation in the labour market and of the possibilities of employment training is to provide an overview of the labour market, positions and the requirements set for employment in the positions and of the possibilities of employment training in order to enable persons to choose the most suitable job or the most purposeful employment service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;vahendus </eesti>
<inglise>Employment mediation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;vahendus on vabale t&ouml;&ouml;kohale vajalike oskustega t&ouml;&ouml;taja leidmine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employment mediation means finding an employee with the necessary skills to a vacant position. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;vahenduse eesm&auml;rk on t&ouml;&ouml;otsijale sobiva t&ouml;&ouml; ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale sobivaima t&ouml;&ouml;taja leidmine ning v&auml;iksema konkurentsiv&otilde;imega t&ouml;&ouml;tu t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendumise soodustamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The purpose of employment mediation is to find suitable work for persons who seek employment and the most suitable employees for employers, and to favour the employment of less competitive unemployed persons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turukoolitus </eesti>
<inglise>Employment training </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;turukoolitus on &otilde;pe, milles osalev t&ouml;&ouml;otsija omandab v&otilde;i t&auml;iendab kutse-, eri- ja ametialaseid teadmisi, oskusi ja vilumusi v&otilde;i kohaneb t&ouml;&ouml;turu n&otilde;uetega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employment training means training in the course of which a person who seeks employment and participates in the training acquires or develops vocational, professional and occupational knowledge, skills and experience or adapts to the requirements of the labour market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigi t&ouml;&ouml;turuasutuste &uuml;lesanne t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolituse korraldamisel on t&ouml;&ouml;otsija konkurentsiv&otilde;ime t&otilde;stmine t&ouml;&ouml;turul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In organisation of employment training, the function of state employment agencies is to increase the competitiveness of persons who seek employment in the labour market. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja tellib t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolitust haridusasutuselt v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;siliselt v&otilde;i juriidiliselt isikult, kellel on koolitusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Employment service providers shall order employment training from educational institutions or natural or legal persons who hold education licences. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja s&otilde;lmib koolituse tellimiseks koolitajaga lepingu, milles m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The employment service provider shall enter into a contract with a training provider for ordering training services, which shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koolitusest osav&otilde;tjate arv; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the number of participants in the training; </inglise>
<eesti>2) koolituse aeg ja kestus &otilde;ppetundides ning &otilde;ppekava; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the time and duration of the training in training hours and the training plan; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &otilde;petatavad oskused ja nende kavandatav tase ning &otilde;ppetulemuse hindamise viis; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the skills to be taught and the planned level thereof and the method of assessment of training results; </inglise>
<eesti>4) koolituse kogumaksumus ja &uuml;he osav&otilde;tja &uuml;he &otilde;ppetunni hind; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the total cost of the training and cost per person per one training hour; </inglise>
<eesti>5) koolituse eest maksmise tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the conditions of payment for the training. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Koolitaja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Training providers are required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) pidama individuaalset arvestust koolitusest osav&otilde;tu ja &otilde;ppet&ouml;&ouml; tulemuste kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) maintain individual records of attendance and training results; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kinni pidama &otilde;ppekavast; </eesti>
<inglise>2) adhere to the training plan; </inglise>
<eesti>3) andma koolituse l&auml;bimise kohta t&otilde;endi v&otilde;i tunnistuse. </eesti>
<inglise>3) issue a certificate or report concerning completion of training. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveamet tellib t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolitust, mille kestus on kuni kuus kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An employment office shall order employment training the duration of which is up to six months. </inglise>
<eesti>Pikema kestusega koolituse v&otilde;ib tellida, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tule on tagatud t&ouml;&ouml;koht ning kuut kuud &uuml;letava koolitusosa eest tasub tulevane t&ouml;&ouml;andja sellekohase lepingu alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Training the duration of which is longer may be ordered if a job shall be ensured to the unemployed person, and the future employer shall pay for the portion of training which exceeds the six months on the basis of a corresponding contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) T&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja on kohustatud koolituse taseme hindamiseks tutvuma koolituse korraldamisega ning tal on &otilde;igus kaasata selleks eksperte ja korraldada k&uuml;sitlusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Employment service providers are required to review the organisation of training in order to evaluate the level of training, and they have the right to engage experts and make inquiries for that purpose. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetus ettev&otilde;tluse alustamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Employment subsidy to start business </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetust ettev&otilde;tluse alustamiseks antakse t&ouml;&ouml;tule. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employment subsidy to start a business is granted to an unemployed person. </inglise>
<eesti>Toetuse eesm&auml;rk on aidata luua uusi kvaliteetseid t&ouml;&ouml;kohti ja toetada ettev&otilde;tluse alustamist. </eesti>
<inglise>The purpose of the subsidy is to promote the creation of quality employment and to support the starting of businesses. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametist v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetust taotleda t&ouml;&ouml;tu, kes vastab &uuml;heaegselt j&auml;rgmistele tingimustele: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Unemployed persons who meet all the following requirements may apply for employment subsidies from employment offices: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kelle vanus on 18 aastat v&otilde;i &uuml;le selle kuni vanaduspensionieani; </eesti>
<inglise>1) persons who have attained at least 18 years of age and are under pensionable age; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kes on l&auml;binud ettev&otilde;tluskoolituse v&otilde;i kellel on ettev&otilde;tluskogemusi. </eesti>
<inglise>2) persons who have undergone business training or who have experience in business. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ettev&otilde;tluse alustamiseks t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetust taotlev t&ouml;&ouml;tu esitab t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametile: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An unemployed person who applies for an employment subsidy to start a business shall submit to an employment office the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avalduse; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an application; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &auml;riplaani; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a business plan; </inglise>
<eesti>3) dokumendid, mis t&otilde;endavad ettev&otilde;tluskoolituse l&auml;bimist v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tluskogemust. </eesti>
<inglise>3) documents certifying that the person has undergone business training or has experience in business. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetuse andmise otsuse teeb t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveamet koos kohaliku omavalitsuse ja Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse esindajaga t&ouml;&ouml;tu avalduse saamisest alates 15 t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employment office shall make a decision on grant of an employment subsidy together with the representatives of the local government and the local Tax Board Office within fifteen working days as of receipt of an application of the person who seeks employment. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus vormistatakse protokollina, mis on t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveameti ja taotleja vahelise lepingu s&otilde;lmimise alus. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision shall be prepared as a report which is the basis for a contract between the employment office and the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingu vormi kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the standard format for contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveamet kannab t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetuse t&ouml;&ouml;tu pangakontole. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An employment office shall transfer an employment subsidy to the bank account of the person who seeks employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetust saanud isik on kohustatud seda kasutama sihtotstarbeliselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A person who receives an employment subsidy is required to use the subsidy for the intended purpose. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) T&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveamet kontrollib t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetust saanud isiku majandustegevust ja toetuse kasutamise sihtotstarbelisust toetuse &uuml;lekandmisest alates v&auml;hemalt kaks korda aastas. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) An employment office shall monitor the economic activities of the person who receives an employment subsidy and the use of the subsidy for the intended purpose at least twice a year as of transfer of the employment subsidy. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetus tuleb tagastada, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(8) An employment subsidy shall be returned if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &auml;riplaanis etten&auml;htud majandustegevus ei alga t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetuse &uuml;lekandmisest alates kolme kuu jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the economic activities prescribed in the business plan are not commenced within three months as of transfer of the employment subsidy; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &auml;riplaanis kavandatud majandustegevus l&otilde;peb enne &uuml;he aasta m&ouml;&ouml;dumist t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetuse &uuml;lekandmisest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the economic activities planned in the business plan terminate before the end of one year as of transfer of the employment subsidy; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetust saanud isik v&otilde;&otilde;randab talle kuuluva osaku toetuse abil loodud &auml;ri&uuml;hingu p&otilde;hikapitalist toetuse &uuml;lekandmisest alates &uuml;he aasta jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the person who receives the employment subsidy transfers his or her share of the fixed capital of the commercial undertaking founded with the aid of subsidy within one year as of grant of the subsidy; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetust ei kasutata sihtotstarbeliselt. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the employment subsidy is not used for the intended purposes. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetuse suuruse kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) The Government of the Republic shall establish the amount of employment subsidies. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetust ei anta olemasoleva ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i &auml;ri&uuml;hingu majandustegevuse alustamiseks ega selle osanikuks v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;riks astumiseks ega isikule, kelle asutatud ettev&otilde;te on pankrotistunud v&otilde;i kellel on maksuv&otilde;lg riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ees v&otilde;i kui esitatud &auml;riplaan on suure riskiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) Employment subsidies shall not be granted to start the economic activities of an existing enterprise or commercial undertaking, to acquire the shares of an enterprise or commercial undertaking, or to a person whose enterprise is bankrupt or who owes taxes to the state or local government or if the submitted business plan involves great risk. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetuse andmisest keeldumise otsus peab sisaldama keeldumise p&otilde;hjendust. </eesti>
<inglise>A decision to refuse to grant an employment subsidy shall contain the reasons for refusal. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetus t&ouml;&ouml;andjale </eesti>
<inglise>Employment subsidies to employers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetus on t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveameti kaudu t&ouml;&ouml;andjale antav raha v&auml;iksema konkurentsiv&otilde;imega t&ouml;&ouml;tu t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employment subsidy is money allocated to employers through an employment office to employ less competitive unemployed persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andjale t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetuse maksmise eesm&auml;rk on toetada v&auml;iksema konkurentsiv&otilde;imega t&ouml;&ouml;tu t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendumist ja t&ouml;&ouml;tamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The purpose of paying employment subsidies to employers is to support the employment and working of less competitive unemployed persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;iksema konkurentsiv&otilde;imega t&ouml;&ouml;tuks loetakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following are deemed to be less competitive unemployed persons: </inglise>
<eesti>1) osaliselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu isik; </eesti>
<inglise>1) persons who are partially incapacitated for work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) rase v&otilde;i isik, kes kasvatab alla kuue aasta vanust last; </eesti>
<inglise>2) pregnant women and persons who raise children under 6 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>3) 16-24-aastane noor; </eesti>
<inglise>3) young persons between 16 and 24 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>4) isik, kellel on vanaduspensionieani j&auml;&auml;nud kuni viis aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>4) persons who attain pensionable age within five years; </inglise>
<eesti>5) vanglast vabanenud isik; </eesti>
<inglise>5) persons released from prison; </inglise>
<eesti>6) pikaajaline t&ouml;&ouml;tu. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the long-term unemployed. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetust v&otilde;ib taotleda t&ouml;&ouml;andja, kes v&otilde;tab t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;i teenistusse v&auml;iksema konkurentsiv&otilde;imega t&ouml;&ouml;tu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employer who hires or employs in service a less competitive unemployed person may apply for an employment subsidy. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) V&auml;iksema konkurentsiv&otilde;imega t&ouml;&ouml;tu t&auml;ist&ouml;&ouml;ajaga t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamise korral t&ouml;&ouml;andjale makstava t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetuse suurus on: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The amount of the employment subsidy for an employer who employs a less competitive unemployed person full-time shall be: </inglise>
<eesti>1) esimese kuue kuu jooksul kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;r kuus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) during the first six months, the minimum monthly wage per month; </inglise>
<eesti>2) j&auml;rgmise kuue kuu jooksul 50 protsenti kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;rast kuus. </eesti>
<inglise>2) during the following six months, 50 per cent of the minimum monthly wage per month. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetuse maksmise alus on t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja vahel s&otilde;lmitud leping. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The basis for payment of an employment subsidy is a contract entered into between the employment service provider and the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingu vormi kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the standard format for contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) T&ouml;&ouml;turutoetust makstakse &uuml;he aasta v&auml;ltel kord kuus t&ouml;&ouml;andja esitatud t&ouml;&ouml;ajatabeli ja palgat&otilde;endi alusel vastavalt t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuse osutaja ning t&ouml;&ouml;andja vahel s&otilde;lmitud lepingule. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) An employment subsidy shall be paid every month for the period of one year on the basis of a time calculation table and statement of wages submitted by the employer pursuant to the contract entered into between the employment service provider and the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) T&ouml;&ouml;andja peab t&ouml;&ouml;turutoetuse tagastama t&auml;ies ulatuses, kui t&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petatakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel enne &uuml;he aasta m&ouml;&ouml;dumist, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(8) An employer shall return an employment subsidy in full if the employment contract is terminated on the initiative of the employer before the end of one year except if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vabastamise p&otilde;hjus on t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I I993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32; 1998, 111, 1829; 1999, 16, 276; 60, 616; 2000, 25, 144; 51, 321; 57, 370; 102, 669; 2001, 17, 78; 42, 233) &sect; 86 punktide 6-8 ja 12 alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the reason for release is termination of an employment contract pursuant to clauses 86 6) -8) or 12) of the Employment Contracts Act (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I I993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32; 1998, 111, 1829; 1999, 16, 276; 60, 616; 2000, 25, 144; 51, 327; 57, 370; 102, 669; 2001, 17, 78; 42, 233); </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;taja ei vasta ametikohale v&otilde;i tehtavale t&ouml;&ouml;le oma t&ouml;&ouml;oskuse v&otilde;i tervise poolest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the employee is unsuitable for his or her position or the work to be performed due to professional skills or for reasons of health; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &auml;ri&uuml;hing likvideeritakse v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja l&otilde;petab oma tegevuse. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the company is liquidated or the sole proprietor terminates his or her activities. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>H&auml;daabit&ouml;&ouml; </eesti>
<inglise>Community placements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) H&auml;daabit&ouml;&ouml; on ajutine tasuline t&ouml;&ouml;, mille tegemiseks ei ole &uuml;ldjuhul vaja kutse-, eriala- ega ametialast ettevalmistust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Community placements are temporary paid jobs which generally do not require vocational, professional or occupational training. </inglise>
<eesti>H&auml;daabit&ouml;&ouml;le ei kohaldata t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;igusakte, v&auml;lja arvatud t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse seadus (RT I 1999, 60, 616; 2000, 55, 362; 2001, 17, 78) ning t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja seadus (RT I 1994, 2, 12; 1995, 12, 120). </eesti>
<inglise>Labour laws do not apply to community placements except the Occupational Health and Safety Act (RT I 1999, 60, 616; 2000, 55, 362; 2001, 17, 78) and the Working and Rest Time Act (RT I 1994, 2, 12; 1995, 12, 120). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) H&auml;daabit&ouml;&ouml;d korraldab t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveamet valitsusasutuse hallatava riigiasutuse v&otilde;i omavalitsus&uuml;ksusega s&otilde;lmitud lepingu alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employment office shall organise community placements on the basis of a contract with a state agency administered by a government agency or with a local government. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingus m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks h&auml;daabit&ouml;&ouml; laad, t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskoht ja t&ouml;&ouml; kestus, rakendatavate t&ouml;&ouml;tute arv ning nende palk ja selle maksmise tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>The contract shall determine the nature of the community placement, the place of work, the duration of work, the number of unemployed persons to be employed, the wages and the conditions for payment thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveamet on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;tule enne tema h&auml;daabit&ouml;&ouml;le saatmist tutvustama t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga s&otilde;lmitud lepingut ning tema &otilde;igusi ja kohustusi h&auml;daabit&ouml;&ouml;l osalemise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employment office is required to acquaint an unemployed person with the contract entered into with the employer before referring the person to a community placement, and with his or her rights and obligations during participation in the community placement. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) H&auml;daabit&ouml;&ouml;l osalevale t&ouml;&ouml;tule maksab tasu h&auml;daabit&ouml;&ouml; korraldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The person who organises community placements shall pay remuneration to unemployed persons participating in the community placements. </inglise>
<eesti>H&auml;daabit&ouml;&ouml; tunnitasu alamm&auml;&auml;ra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The Government of the Republic shall establish the minimum hourly wage for community placements. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsen&otilde;ustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Vocational guidance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kutsen&otilde;ustamine on t&ouml;&ouml;otsijale tema haridusele, t&ouml;&ouml;oskustele ja isikuomadustele vastava t&ouml;&ouml; v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendumiseks vajaliku t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolituse soovitamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Vocational guidance means recommending to a person who seeks employment employment which suits his or her education, professional skills and personal characteristics, or employment training which is necessary for engagement in employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kutsen&otilde;ustamise eesm&auml;rk on aidata t&ouml;&ouml;otsijal lahendada t&ouml;&ouml; valikuga, t&ouml;&ouml;alase karj&auml;&auml;ri ning t&ouml;&ouml; saamise v&otilde;i kaotamisega seotud k&uuml;simusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The purpose of vocational guidance is to assist persons who seek employment to resolve issues related to choosing work, professional career, and access to or loss of employment. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kutsen&otilde;ustajal peab olema k&otilde;rgharidus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Persons providing vocational guidance must have completed higher education. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
