<eesti>Rahastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Financing </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi t&ouml;&ouml;turuasutuste &uuml;lalpidamist ja t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenuste osutamist rahastatakse riigieelarvest. </eesti>
<inglise>Maintenance of state employment agencies and provision of employment services shall be financed from the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Eba&otilde;igete andmete esitamisega saadu h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for services received by submission of incorrect information </inglise>
<eesti>Eba&otilde;igete andmete esitamisega t&ouml;&ouml;turuteenust saanud isik on kohustatud saadu h&uuml;vitama. </eesti>
<inglise>A person who receives employment services by submission of incorrect information is required to compensate for the received services. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Resolution of disputes </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse kohaldamisel tekkivad vaidlused lahendab kohus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Disputes arising from application of this Act are resolved by a court. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pooltel on &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda kohtusse nelja kuu jooksul, alates p&auml;evast, millal nad on saanud v&otilde;i oleksid pidanud teada saama oma &otilde;iguste rikkumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Parties have the right of recourse to a court during four months from the day on which they became or should have become aware of a violation of their rights. </inglise>
